parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to drift or steer unexpectedly, leading to loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The power steering feels stuck or locked
the vehicle drifts or steers unexpectedly
the steering feels heavy or difficult to turn
the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering jerks or overcorrects
and the vehicle's console displays error codes or warning lights.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause the vehicle to lose directional control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The steering feels stuck or locked
the vehicle drifts or steers unexpectedly
the steering feels heavy or difficult to turn
the vehicle pulls to one side
and the steering jerks or overcorrects.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the DPS unit can cause the power steering system to malfunction, leading to loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The power steering feels stuck or locked
the vehicle drifts or steers unexpectedly
the steering feels heavy or difficult to turn
the vehicle pulls to one side
and the steering jerks or overcorrects.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fuel system fire can cause a vehicle to engulf in flames, posing a significant risk to the driver and passengers, potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly catches fire
often near the fuel tank or seat area
with flames spreading quickly
and in some cases
accompanied by a popping sound or smoke.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine overheating can cause the vehicle to enter limp mode, leading to rapid deceleration, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially on high-speed roads. In extreme cases, it can also cause fires, resulting in vehicle destruction and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Engine overheating
limp mode activation
rapid deceleration
loss of power
engine stalling
warning lights or messages on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fire Hazard due to Heat Shield Ignition
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ignition of the foil-foam heat shield can cause fires, resulting in vehicle destruction and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Engine compartment fires
smoke or flames emanating from the exhaust pipe area
burning smell or odors.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause the vehicle to stall or catch fire, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Engine stalling
electrical system malfunctions
warning lights or messages on the dashboard
burning smells or odors.
